<table class="metadata plainlinks mbox-small" style="border:1px solid #aaa; background-color:#f9f9f9;">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image"><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:Search/White_noise" title="commons:Special:Search/White noise"><img alt="Sister project" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/40px-Commons-logo.svg.png" width="40" height="54" border="0" /></a></td>
<td class="mbox-text" style=""><a href="/wiki/Wikimedia_Commons" title="Wikimedia Commons">Wikimedia Commons</a> has media related to: <b><i><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:White_noise" class="extiw" title="commons:Category:White noise">White noise</a> </i></b></td>
</tr>
</table>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.elec.qmul.ac.uk/staffinfo/markp/2003/OjaPlumbley03-ica2003.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.elec.qmul.ac.uk/staffinfo/markp/2003/OjaPlumbley03-ica2003.pdf" rel="nofollow">A mathematical application of noise whitening of pictures</a></li>
<li><a href="http://whitenoisemp3s.com/?p=22" class="external text" title="http://whitenoisemp3s.com/?p=22" rel="nofollow">White noise in wave(.wav) format</a>, 1 minute long</li>
<li><a href="http://www.sengpielaudio.com/calculator-noise.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.sengpielaudio.com/calculator-noise.htm" rel="nofollow">White noise calculator, thermal noise</a>, Voltage in microvolts, conversion to noise level in dBu and dBV and vice versa</li>
<li><a href="http://socrates.berkeley.edu/~phylabs/bsc/Supplementary/NoiseGenerator.html" class="external text" title="http://socrates.berkeley.edu/~phylabs/bsc/Supplementary/NoiseGenerator.html" rel="nofollow">Noise generator</a>, a generator to explore different types of noise</li>
<li><a href="http://www.audiocheck.net" class="external text" title="http://www.audiocheck.net" rel="nofollow">A free collection of online test tones</a>, white noise and more</li>
<li><a href="http://code.google.com/p/noisy/" class="external text" title="http://code.google.com/p/noisy/" rel="nofollow">Noisy</a>, an open-source white noise generator for Mac OS X Leopard</li>
<li><a href="http://simplynoise.com" class="external text" title="http://simplynoise.com" rel="nofollow">Simply Noise</a>, a free online white, pink and brown/red noise generator, uses Flash</li>
<li><a href="http://www.phoxware.com/2009/02/vibes-iphone/" class="external text" title="http://www.phoxware.com/2009/02/vibes-iphone/" rel="nofollow">Vibes</a>, an application for the iPhone which plays different types of white noise</li>
</ul>


